      "side": 1,
      "message": "The Reset method and a property write to maxint are not semantically equivalent at the hardware layer:\n\n- Writing maxint to RequestedSpeedLimit*Hz is a value write — the daemon forwards the actual integer (2^64 - 1) to the device firmware as a clock limit. The firmware doesn\u0027t know about the PDI maxint convention; many devices either reject the out-of-range value or interpret it as a literal limit.\n\n- The Redfish Control.ResetToDefaults action also expresses this \"remove the setting\" semantic rather than \"write a sentinel\".\n\nSeparating the two keeps the caller\u0027s intent explicit and matches both the Redfish action model and the underlying device command. Happy to revisit if you\u0027d prefer a different approach.",
      "parentUuid": "bb83b669_fb29169e",
